The paper focuses on motion planning in robotics, which is a core topic in the field of robotics (cs.RO). The use of deep learning and reinforcement learning algorithms for motion planning also falls under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of images in the input, which suggests the involvement of computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper discusses the application of the proposed method in rapidly changing environments, which is relevant to the field of control systems (cs.SY).
